# Lumiverb — Testing & Environment Rules

## Test-Driven
- Every feature implementation must be accompanied by a pytest test file.
- Every Alembic migration must have a corresponding test in `tests/test_migrations.py` that:
  1. Uses `testcontainers` to start a fresh Postgres instance
  2. Runs `alembic upgrade head`
  3. Runs `alembic downgrade base` (or `-1`) to verify reversibility

## Test Marks — Required on Every Test
- `@pytest.mark.fast` — no DB, no AI, pure unit tests, mocks, `tmp_path` only
- `@pytest.mark.slow` — requires DB via testcontainers Postgres
- `@pytest.mark.ai` — requires Moondream Station running locally
- `@pytest.mark.quickwit` — requires dev Quickwit at port 7281

Never leave a test without a mark. Tests must never touch port 7280 (production Quickwit).

## Test Data
- Tests that write to a shared database must use unique identifiers (ULIDs, UUIDs,
  or secrets.token_urlsafe) for all created records to avoid state bleed between
  tests in the same module.
- Never use hardcoded IDs or predictable values like "test-tenant-1" as primary keys
  in tests — these will collide when fixtures are scoped to module or session.
- Fixture scope preference: use `scope="module"` for container/engine fixtures,
  `scope="function"` for sessions if rollback isolation is needed, but prefer
  module-scoped sessions when tests use unique IDs and don't interfere.

## Environment
- Package manager is `uv`. Always show full `uv` commands — never bare `python` or `pip`.
- Always use `uv sync --all-extras` — never plain `uv sync` (it drops the dev environment).
- Docker Compose manages infrastructure (Postgres + Quickwit).
- The API server and workers run outside Docker in development.

## Timestamps
- All timestamps stored `WITH TIME ZONE`. Never local time.
- Display in local time only at the UI layer.
